@Node Description

	@{u}@{b}Short description of S-Index Manager@{ub}@{uu}



S-Index Manager has been created to manage Searcher index files. It allows you to :
 @{bg fill}   @{bg background} Create index.
 @{bg fill}   @{bg background} Update index.
 @{bg fill}   @{bg background} Convert old Searcher index to new format.
 @{bg fill}   @{bg background} Show date and hour of index creation.
 @{bg fill}   @{bg background} Delete index.
 @{bg fill}   @{bg background} Show the status of index (if it is complet or not).
 @{bg fill}   @{bg background} Use @{"ToolType/CLI argument" link ToolTypes}


S-Index Manager is a part of a @{b}shareware@{ub} archive. See the documentation of Searcher for more details.


@Endnode

@Node Config "Requirements"

	@{u}@{b}S-Index Manager needs :@{ub}@{uu}

@{bg fill}   @{bg background} OS 2.0 or greater.
@{bg fill}   @{bg background} ReqTools.library © Nico François.

	@{u}@{b}S-Index Manager use if present :@{ub}@{uu}

@{bg fill}   @{bg background} @{i}locale.library@{ui} and @{i}sindexmanager.catalog@{ui}.


@Endnode

@Node Installation "How to install S-Index Manager ?"

	@{u}@{b}Installation@{ub}@{uu}



No @{i}Installer@{ui} script !

@{b}Just copy :@{ub}
 @{bg fill}   @{bg background} @{i}sindexmanager.catalog@{ui} in @{i}LOCALE:catalogs/VotreLangue/@{ui}


@Endnode

@Node FenetreA "Main window"

	@{u}@{b}Description of the main window@{ub}@{uu}

 

@{b}First list :@{ub} this is the list of index files presents in the current dyrectory

@{b}Second list :@{ub} here appears informations about the current index.

@{b}Create Index :@{ub} ask for the name of the new indew file. Newt ask for the directory to use. Then create the index as Searcher.

@{b}Update Index :@{ub} create again the current index.

@{b}Delete Index :@{ub} no comment...

@{b}Convert old index :@{ub} the old index don't have the extra informations of the extended format. This command adds just add this.

@{b}Scan directory :@{ub} update the list of index files in the current directory.

@{b}Change directory :@{ub} change the current directory.


@Endnode

@Node ToolTypes "Tooltypes and CLI arguments"

	@{b}Note@{ub}


If a tooltype is disable (with()), a default value is used.




	@{b}ToolTypes and CLI arguments supported by S-Index Manager :@{ub}



@{b}INDEXPATH=@{ub} : this is the path used for all the operations on index files.


@Endnode

